node.text: I got momentarily excited and thought you were selling kuehs again! Your kuehs inspired me to try making my own, but it's not the same :( the abacus seeds look great !
@jinlow hahaha sorry to disappoint you! Hope you give the abacus seeds a try and let me know if you develop your own tips!

Hi guys! I’m bringing this account back from the dead. No, I’m not re-opening my business! I feel encouraged that so many of us are emerging from CB much better cooks than before, so I thought I’d use this account to document my home cooking and share my learnings! It’s a fun little experiment so let’s just see how it goes.

First up, suan pan zi or abacus seeds. It’s a traditional Hakka dish that I’ve only recently attempted. I’m ashamed to admit I’ve made gnocchi more times than I’ve made abacus seeds! Check out my highlights for more.

Stay safe everyone! And keep cooking!

Sharon
